@kboronski-ant some of the recent fork changes have broken function_fork_valid in sv-tests, with "Unknown node type reached emitter" might you take a look?  (All other tests that passed before seem to still pass.)

```
/*
:name: function_fork_valid
:description: function valid fork test
:tags: 13.4.4
:type: simulation elaboration parsing
*/
module t();

function int fun(int val);
	fork
		$display("abc");
		$display("def");
	join_none
	return val + 2;
endfunction

initial begin
	$display("$d", fun(2));
        $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
        $finish;
end
endmodule
```
